<p>Central government spending actually declined in the pandemic year 2020-­21, according to the government’s own report to the IMF.</p>
<p>Falling demand - private final consumption expenditure (PFCE) + Public spending</p>
<hr />
<ul>
<li>CONSTRAINTS to spending more
<ul>
<li>Interest payment = 45% of revenue&nbsp;</li>
<li>Debt / GDP&nbsp;&nbsp;= &gt;85%&nbsp;</li></ul></li>
<li>OPPORTUNITES To spend
<ul>
<li>NIP -&gt;&nbsp; rs. 350 trn on infra by 2030 needed&nbsp;</li>
<li>NIP = infra needed rs 111 trn in 2021-25</li>
<li>&nbsp;</li></ul></li></ul>

<p>Thus need alternative way for revenue. Asset Monetisation imperative.</p>

